                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d807">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hunter</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-07-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 21, 1899</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Hunter reports, in connection with his telegram of the 6th instant, the
                    receipt of the promised copy of the proceedings in the trial of the sentinel who
                    killed Mr. Pears, and that the Government of Honduras persists in its denial of
                    responsibility for Pears’s death and its refusal to demand for indemnity.</p>
                <p>He asks if correspondence in relation to the matter shall be transmitted and
                    Department’s instructions awaited.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
